    {
      "reviewerId": null,
      "reviewerUrl": null,
      "name": null,
      "reviewerNumberOfReviews": 3,
      "isLocalGuide": false,
      "reviewerPhotoUrl": null,
      "text": "When my father, 72, underwent major intestinal surgery and had a stoma fitted, our family faced a challenge. With nearly everyone working and young children to care for, we couldn’t provide him with round-the-clock support or proper stoma care. Sadly, this led to a wound infection and a second hospital admission. Thankfully, after his discharge, we found Fu Ka Centre. We arranged for him to stay there for a month, and it made all the difference. Little by little, his condition improved and his wound healed well. He is now slowly returning to his normal routine. We are deeply grateful to Fu Ka Centre.",
